Create a repository or a file
Terminal : cd myDir 
           git clone repository URL
If testing features, create a new fork/branch

Commands:
git clone URL -> clone project in dir on local
git status -> differences
git add file.php or (.) or -A
git commit -m "message between quotes"
git push -> put on version control
git pull -> get from version control 

git -> gives all available commands

If stuck (forgot the -m for commit) press esc ; wq 

Start using git!
